Hello,

Please find attached the Department=E2=80=99s Request for Local Response fo=
r PRS
15514. The District=E2=80=99s Local Response is due to the Department on Ap=
ril 7,
2026. The Complainant may submit additional information and documentation
about their allegations until April 7, 2026.  While PRS is required to
consider all information related to a complaint investigation, PRS may not
consider, at its discretion, any information submitted late or untimely.

Should the Department require supplemental information upon review of the
information submitted by the Parties, the Department will contact the party
from which it is seeking information with a specific request and will
provide a date by which this supplemental information must be provided.

Parties are encouraged to continue to work together to resolve their
disputes before, during, and after a complaint has been filed. If the
parties reach a local agreement, they may provide notice of the agreement
to PRS by using the Local Agreement Notice
<https://www.doe.mass.edu/prs/agreements/default.html>.

Thank you,

Nick


